casebody.data:
The State of Ohio, Appellee, v. Koogler, Appellant.

[Cite as State v. Koogler (1999), 87 Ohio St.3d 1206.]

(No. 98-2292 Submitted August 25, 1999 Decided October 13, 1999.) Ron O’Brien, Franklin County Prosecuting Attorney, and Steven L. Taylor, Assistant Prosecuting Attorney, for appellee. Judith M. Stevenson, Franklin County Public Defender, and Paul Skendelas, Assistant Public Defender, for appellant.

The cause is dismissed, sua sponte, as having been improvidently allowed.

Moyer, C.J., Douglas, Resnick, F.E. Sweeney, Pfeifer, Cook and Lundberg Stratton, JJ., concur.
